==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mesoderm
<hw>Mes"o*derm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Meso-</ets> +
Gr. <grk>de`rma</grk> skin.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>The layer of the blastoderm, between the ectoderm and endoderm;
mesoblast. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Blastoderm</er> and
<er>Ectoderm</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The middle body layer in some
invertebrates.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>The middle layer of tissue in
some vegetable structures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mesodermal</ent>⟦br⟧
